data.enText: extra help or support that you can get if necessary

data.chText: 警方得到了军方的增援。
data.enText: The police had backup from the army.

data.chText: 如果有参赛者退出，我们可以用他作为替补。
data.enText: We can use him as a backup if one of the other players drops out.
a copy of a file, etc. that can be used if the original is lost or damaged

data.chText: 每次都要对文件进行备份。
data.enText: Always make a backup of your work.

tr: the act of providing approval and support
example: his vigorous backing of the conservatives got him in trouble with progressives

tr: (computer science) a copy of a file or directory on a separate storage device
example: he made a backup in case the original was accidentally damaged or erased

tr: a musical part (vocal or instrumental) that supports or provides background for other musical parts
someone who takes the place of another (as when things get dangerous or difficult)
example: the star had a stand-in for dangerous scenes
we need extra employees for summer fill-ins

tr: an accumulation caused by clogging or a stoppage
example: a traffic backup on the main street
he discovered a backup in the toilet

value.def: Backup consists of extra equipment, resources, or people that you can get help or support from if necessary.

example.ex: There is no emergency back-up immediately available...
example.tran: 手头无法获得应急支持。

example.ex: Alternative treatments can provide a useful back-up to conventional treatment.
example.tran: 替代疗法能为传统的治疗提供有效的辅助。

value.def: If you have something such as a second piece of equipment or set of plans as backup, you have arranged for them to be available for use in case the first one does not work.

example.ex: Every part of the system has a backup...
example.tran: 系统的每个部分都有备用元件。

example.ex: Computer users should make regular back-up copies of their work.
example.tran: 计算机使用者应该定期对自己的工作进行备份。
